# Version Numbering — Limitless Cost Estimator

Every time a change is made to the plugin, update the version number in **two places** in `limitless-cost-estimator.php` before committing:

1. The plugin header comment: `* Version: X.X.X`
2. The PHP constant: `define( 'LCE_VERSION', 'X.X.X' );`

## Version Format: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH

| Change type | Bump | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Bug fix or small tweak | PATCH | 1.2.1 → 1.2.2 |
| New feature or behavioral change | MINOR | 1.2.1 → 1.3.0 |
| Major redesign or breaking change | MAJOR | 1.2.1 → 2.0.0 |

## Commit Message Format

```
v1.2.2 - Short description of what changed
- Bullet point explaining each change
- Keep it clear enough to understand without reading the code
```

## Rules

- Always commit after every meaningful change — never batch unrelated changes into one commit.
- Both version locations must match exactly.
- The CSS and JS files are cache-busted using `LCE_VERSION`, so bumping the version also forces browsers to load fresh assets.
